# UART Transmitter and Receiver in Verilog

## Overview

This project implements a parameterized Universal Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter (UART) in Verilog HDL. The design consists of independent transmitter and receiver modules, a configurable baud rate generator, a top-level integration module, and comprehensive testbenches for module-level and system-level verification.

The UART follows the standard asynchronous serial communication protocol with the following configuration:

- 8 Data Bits
- No Parity
- 1 Stop Bit (8N1)
- LSB First
- Parameterized Baud Rate

---

## Features

- Parameterized baud rate generator
- UART transmitter FSM
- UART receiver FSM
- Mid-bit start bit validation
- Framing error detection
- One-clock transmit done pulse
- One-clock receive done pulse
- Loopback verification
- Modular and reusable RTL
- Fully synthesizable design

---

